data.enText: a line, route, or journey around a place

data.chText: 比赛以环绕城中心跑八圈结束。
data.enText: The race ended with eight laps of a city centre circuit.

data.chText: 地球绕太阳运行一周需要一年的时间。
data.enText: The earth takes a year to make a circuit of (= go around) the sun.
the complete path of wires and equipment along which an electric current flows
a circuit diagram (= one showing all the connections in the different parts of the circuit )
a series of games or matches in which the same players regularly take part
a track for cars or motorcycles to race around
a series of places or events of a particular kind at which the same people appear or take part

data.chText: 巡回讲学 / 卡巴莱歌舞巡回表演

data.enText: a regular journey made by a judge to hear court cases in each of the courts of law in a particular area

simple_means.memory_skill: circu〔= circ〕圆，环 + it 走 → 环行；电路

example: he drove an extra lap just for insurance

tr: a journey or route all the way around a particular place or area
example: they took an extended tour of Europe
we took a quick circuit of the park
a ten-day coach circuit of the island

tr: an electrical device that provides a path for electrical current to flow
(law) a judicial division of a state or the United States (so-called because originally judges traveled and held court in different locations)
one of the twelve groups of states in the United States that is covered by a particular circuit court of appeals
the boundary line encompassing an area or object
example: he had walked the full circumference of his land
a danger to all races over the whole circumference of the globe

tr: an established itinerary of venues or events that a particular group of people travel to
example: she's a familiar name on the club circuit
the judge makes a circuit of the courts in his district
They were circuiting about the state

value.def: An electrical circuit is a complete route which an electric current can flow around.

example.ex: Any attempts to cut through the cabling will break the electrical circuit.
example.tran: 只要一割断电缆，电路就中断。

value.def: A circuit is a series of places that are visited regularly by a person or group, especially as a part of their job.

example.ex: It's a common problem, the one I'm asked about most when I'm on the lecture circuit.
example.tran: 这问题很常见，我在巡回讲演时被问得最多的就是这个问题。

value.tran: （尤指工作时的）巡回线路，巡回，巡游

value.def: A racing circuit is a track on which cars, motorbikes, or cycles race.
A circuit of a place or area is a journey all the way round it.

example.ex: She made a slow circuit of the room.
example.tran: 她绕着房间缓缓地走了一圈。

trans: 循环训练(轮番作不同的体育运动，每种只做很短时间)
逻辑电路(由一系列进行数据运算的逻辑门组成)
(房间或建筑物内的)环形电路
